                        "components": []
                    },
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Extraction",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Extraction",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Biological samples (roots, stems, leaves and flowers from <em>H. citrina</em>) were placed in a lyophilizer for vacuum freeze-drying, and then grind to powder with a grinder. Briefly, 100 mg of powder were weighed and metabolites were extracted by adding 1.2 mL of 70% methanol, vortex once every 30 min, each time lasting for 30 s, a total of 6 times. The sample was placed in the refrigerator at 4 \u00b0C overnight. The mixture was centrifuged at 12,000 rpm for 3 min. Then, the supernatant was filtered by microfiltration membrane (0.22 \u03bcm pore size) for UPLC-MS/MS analysis<strong>[1]</strong>.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Ref:</strong></p><p><strong>[1]</strong> Wang J, Zhang T, Shen X, Liu J, Zhao D, Sun Y, Wang L, Liu Y, Gong X, Liu Y, Zhu ZJ. Serum metabolomics for early diagnosis of esophageal squamous cell carcinoma by UHPLC-QTOF/MS. Metabolomics. 2016 Jul;12:1-0. doi:10.1007/s11306-016-1050-5.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
